# Foundry notes on useful interfaces

Foundry is built around surfaces, signals, structure, and a small number of
deliberate accents. The goal is not to imitate another component library.

## A practical rule

Use hierarchy to explain what matters. Use color to communicate state. Use
motion only when it helps someone understand what changed.
